Usage
:
• Insert brush gently into the space between the teeth at gum level.
• Gently move the brush backwards and forward to remove plaque and debris.
• Never force the brush into a space. If brush is too large try dental floss.
• Rinse brush in water after use. Replace brush regularly.
• The carrying case is ideal for protecting the brush between uses and whilst travelling. For healthy teeth and gums, dentists recommend: * Brush your teeth at least twice a day for 2 minutes, including once before sleeping.
• Daily interdental brushing and flossing to remove food or plaque your toothbrush cannot reach.
• Mouthwash can be used between brushing, to help reduce plaque further.
• Visit your dentist regularly.
• Change your toothbrush every 3 months.

Usage
:
• Insert brush gently into the space between the teeth at gum level.
• Gently move the brush backwards and forward to remove plaque and debris.
• Never force the brush into a space. If brush is too large try dental floss.
• Rinse brush in water after use. Replace brush regularly.
• The carrying case is ideal for protecting the brush between uses and whilst travelling. For healthy teeth and gums, dentists recommend: * Brush your teeth at least twice a day for 2 minutes, including once before sleeping.
• Daily interdental brushing and flossing to remove food or plaque your toothbrush cannot reach.
• Mouthwash can be used between brushing, to help reduce plaque further.
• Visit your dentist regularly.
• Change your toothbrush every 3 months.

Properties
:
My Choice Soya Duck Soft texture, fragrant, delicious stew.
Selected every step.
• Good breed duck - Cherry Valley species from England.
• Farming methods - Independent release in the closed system, certified by the Department of Livestock Development.
• Food - Eat vegetarian food, so clean, not stink.
Manufacturing.

• 100% physical appearance - not bruised, bruised, in good condition Purely plucking Suitable for respecting.

Ingredients
:
Main Ingredients:
Braised Duck with Innards (79.38%)
Duck (1 whole duck with 1 set of innards), seasonings (sugar, iodized salt, dark soy sauce), spices, thickening agent (INS 414), food flavoring additives (disodium 5'-ribonucleotide)
Braised Duck Broth (18.04%)
Water, seasonings (light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, sugar, iodized salt), spices, vegetable oil, thickening agent (INS 414)
Dipping Sauce (2.58%)
Water, sugar, pickled garlic, vinegar, iodized salt, food flavoring additive (monosodium L-glutamate) Allergen Information: Contains wheat flour and soy products.
Usage
:
The trick is to blanch before boiling, so that the duck skin does not fade. Firm and appetizing
• Modern boiling pot Steam and steam pressure systems are distributed evenly and evenly.
• Control your temperature and time to allow the steward to reach the duck meat. With aroma, spice, taste and appetizing color
• Apply to freezing at cold temperatures immediately To maintain quality with modern methods
• Quality control - QA inspections are carried out at factories that produce and randomly lock the products to meet all standards.

Meat & Seafood.details:
Properties
:
Freshness Garantee 100%
Many meat lovers are familiar with beef cuts, but did you know there's another way to divide beef? It's by separating the "Front Quarter" and "Hindquarter" of the cow.
• Front Quarter
What cuts come from the front of the cow?
• Chuck, Rib, Brisket, Plate, Shank
Taste: tender yet chewy, with a satisfying texture due to the abundance of tendons and tissues. The meat flavor is rich and hearty.
Best cooking methods: Ideal for slow-cooking techniques such as braising, smoking, or roasting.
• Hindquarter
What cuts come from the back of the cow?
• Flank, Loin, Round
Taste : soft and easy to chew, with more marbling than the front quarter. The flavor may be less intense, but still delicious.
Best cooking methods: Perfect for grilling, barbecuing, or roasting. Most of these cuts are popular for steaks—a delicious secret worth keeping!

Meat & Seafood.name: Australian Lamb T Bone 1000g.(B
Meat & Seafood.details:
Properties
:
Freshness Garantee 100%
Many meat lovers are familiar with beef cuts, but did you know there's another way to divide beef? It's by separating the "Front Quarter" and "Hindquarter" of the cow.
• Front Quarter
What cuts come from the front of the cow?
• Chuck, Rib, Brisket, Plate, Shank
Taste: tender yet chewy, with a satisfying texture due to the abundance of tendons and tissues. The meat flavor is rich and hearty.
Best cooking methods: Ideal for slow-cooking techniques such as braising, smoking, or roasting.
• Hindquarter
What cuts come from the back of the cow?
• Flank, Loin, Round
Taste : soft and easy to chew, with more marbling than the front quarter. The flavor may be less intense, but still delicious.
Best cooking methods: Perfect for grilling, barbecuing, or roasting. Most of these cuts are popular for steaks—a delicious secret worth keeping!

Fresh Food & Bakery.name: Mainland Vintage Cheese 250g.
Fresh Food & Bakery.details:
Properties
:
Freshness Garantee 100%
Premium quality cheese from New Zealand, aged through the cheese ripening process. This process involves aging the proteins or casein in milk curds over various periods to develop the desired flavors and aromas. Therefore, the aging time has an impact on the taste of the cheese, similar to wine aging – the longer, the better. The cheeses can be categorized as follows:
Mainland Edam Cheese
A cheese with 28% less fat than cheddar cheese, it has a mild flavor and a smooth texture that is easy to enjoy. It is ideal as an appetizer and pairs well with champagne.
Mainland Tasty Cheddar Cheese
Aged for 18 months, this cheese has a rich flavor and a strong cheese aroma. The texture is well-formed, and it is a popular award-winning cheese from New Zealand. It pairs perfectly with white wine.
Mainland Vintage Cheese
For true cheese lovers, this cheese is aged for up to 24 months, resulting in a firm and dense texture with a full-bodied flavor. It is best enjoyed with red wine or red meat steak for a perfect pairing.

Storage instructions
1. After opening, keep pouch tightly closed.

Instructions for preparation and use
1. Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water before preparing formula.

3. Boil fresh water at least 5 minutes. Cool down to warm water (not higher than 40C) prior to mixing
4. Pour desired amount of water into bottle and add powder. Use scoop in box to measure powder.
5. Cap bottle and SHAKE WELL.

Storage instructions (for BIB)
1. After opening, keep pouch tightly closed.
2. Store in a tightly closed container in dry area at room temperature. Do not freeze the powder and avoid excessive heat.
3. Use contents within 1 month after opened.
Storage instructions (for can): Store at room temperature. Do not freeze the powder and avoid excessive heat. Close the lid tightly after use. Store in dry area and use contents within 1 month after opened.

Storage instructions (for can)
Store at room temperature. Do not freeze the powder and avoid excessive heat. Close the lid tightly after use. Store in dry area and use contents within 1 month after opened.

Instructions for preparation and use
1. Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water before preparing formula.
2. Boil clean bottles, nipples, caps and utensils in water at least 10 minutes.
3. Boil fresh water at least 5 minutes. Cool down to warm water (not higher than 40C) prior to mixing
4. Pour desired amount of water into bottle and add powder. Use scoop in box to measure powder.
5. Cap bottle and SHAKE WELL.

Usage
:
1. Use all baits. Break baits apart. Do not remove or puncture labels on bait stations. Place baits wherever you see or have seen roaches. Place baits about 1½ feet away from each other. See diagrams on package for places roaches commonly hide.
2. Place baits properly so they are touching walls or corners. Do not use sprays or foggers around bait stations.
3. Replace all baits every three months, or sooner if roaches return.
